HEADWORD: Ladys bower
<hw>La"dy's bow"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A climbing plant with fragrant blossoms (<spn>Clematis
vitalba</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This term is sometimes applied to other plants of the
same genus.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

